<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98839024634289></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98839024634289><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=98839024634289>RE: Where?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=98839024634289#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=31491><span id= >Pollux</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>13 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 27th 12:50 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The following is a guild I found to be very usefull.<br>NECROMANCER POWER LEVELING 1-50 - Arterius Azmodin, Drinal<br> <br>Hello. First let me introduce myself. I have been playing Everquest since its first release date sometime in late March, early April. Playing since release, the Necromancer has been MY class. I really mean this. After playing&nbsp;&nbsp;for almost 2 years. I currently reside on the Drinal server known as Arterius. I am going to tell you specific spots to level your necromancer faster than anyone else can, regardless of what they tell you. I almost forgot to add, I play Gnome Necromancer only. The Gnome Necromancer is the best Race/Class combo in my opinion because they have many benefits and no dis-advantages. Here we go. <br><br>Level 1-5 is strictly newbie area in Steamfont. Steamfont is the BEST newbie area in the game, do not listen to others saying its Misty. Also, decaying skeletons in the newbie pit give up many bonechips for your further career advancement. Do NOT try to do Kobolds at level 4. Experience will be slow at level 4, but continue to beat on blue newbie monsters.<br><br> At level 5 either group or solo the many Kobold camps in Steamfont until you hit level 6. Finding these camps is part of your exploration. Oh, did I forget to say if you know the lands of Norrath that it can increase your power leveling by 75%? It does. Get to know the lands!<br><br> Once you are level 6, head over to Butcherblock Mountains and kill dwarf skeletons at the druid ring. If this is camped you can always do them at the skeleton tower, but be warned that 2 will have to be killed at once as they are in agro range. <br><br>Once you hit level 8, go back to Steamfont. You WILL need your level 8 Ward Undead spell and Bone Walk (pet) spell before performing the following. Go to the back of Steamfont near the Minotaur caves and the fallen gears. There are 5 static skeleton spawns here that you can easily dispose of with your new pet and Ward Undead. Get that Evocation up, cast, cast, cast! <br><br>Once you hit level 12 you will be finished here. I suggest selling bone chips for 2-4pp per 20. You will need the cash to buy your most important level 12 spells before you need those bone chips themselves. Save some of course for your pet casts. Once you get Bind Affinity, and your level 12 DoT's, go to Freeport. Bind at the dock, get back on the boat and get off on the Sister of Erollisi island (first stop coming into OOT from Freeport). Guard your pet on the very bottom shores and pull sisters to him. Have shadowstep and gate memorized in case of bad pulls or trains. Shadowstep first, then gate. Save those belts and gate back to Freeport when you get 3-4 bags full for FAST cash. Fight here until level 15.<br><br> At level 15 go to Oasis and kill Gators until level 17. At level 17 go to Lake Rathe and solo the Aviak Guard here on the Stone Skeleton island. If it is camped you can always group for the 2-3 spawn areas. You can also find an NPC named Jonah that can give just as good experience. Fight here until level 20. At level 20 go to South Karana and kill the Hermit until 25. If it is camped, kill Aviaks at their village, or go back to Lake Rathe to kill more Aviak Guards (22 at the farthest here). <br><br>Once 25, you can go back to the Sister Island in OOT to kill named sisters at the tree and dock. It is risky and I recommend exploring Kunark and fighting near the windmill with a friend or two to get level 26-27 before doing the sisters. When you do the sisters, however, kill them until level 34. And YES, this is absolutely the FASTEST experience gain you will get in your career. Once 34 you have 4 options. Solo Frogloks in Lower Guk on live side zone. Root, DoT's, Drain when needed. Pull with Screaming Terror to break them up. Zone if in trouble. Your second choice is to group up in Lower Guk dead side zone. Grouping, bah? Really? The experience you gain when grouping is more then soloing at some times depending on the efficiency point your at to dispose of solo NPC's fast enough and have enough mana for the next. So YES, grouping in Lower Guk is very nice experience. Your third choice is to solo the spectre in Feerrott.  I recommend the spectre soloing at 35+. Journeyman boots are a plus. Your fourth choice is to solo an NPC named Cynthia in Lake Rathe at the Gypsy camp. This is a wizard, so buff up. And have those drains ready. You can do all 4 of these choices except for the first until level 45+. <br><br>At 39 though, I recommend fighting the spectre, or Dwarf NPC's in Butherblock as your ONLY solo NPC targets. The best Dwarf NPC which is hardly ever camped is the one residing on a piece of land on the other side of the dock wall. Dru Razbind to be precise. Journeyman Boots are very recommended! Once you are level 45-50 it becomes VERY easy. Solo the Erudite female NPC in front of the Fear Plane gate in Feerrott. You must go through the spectre caves, but at level 45 you can kill them at ease, or sneak by. This is basically all. If you do not know about these places I directed you too, get maps and more maps with locations. Also, you do need to keep a nice intelligence attribute going with equipment finding and questing. I recommend doing all questing and item camping at level 35. Anything before that is a waste and in-efficient. <br> <br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
