	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well your best bet honestly and most game play is if you solo on either camiens, then crocs and so forth.&nbsp;&nbsp;there is an orc camp in oasis at the end of the beach near the Sro boarder not the derv the Orc camp.  there is a spawn there that is lvl 14-20 soloing him shouldnt be to hard he spawns about every 6-8min giving you plenty of time to get mana back and for your pet to heal up, if you want to solo at 16-19 that is your best bet, rarely will you get attacked there by anything at all maybe a puma.  After you hit 19 go to Sro and solo on Dry bone skeletons.  You will have to med a little longer but you can lvl to 21 on them nicely also when you hit lvl20 go and either have a friend make a Troll Shadowknight or make one yourself and buy your lvl 20 pet spell from the Grobb city it costs 13pp and some gold.  I would recommend you stay and lvl off of the Dry bones until you hit 21, then go to the oasis zone again kiss it good bye and hop on the boat to Timour Deep, dont worry as long as you dont kill raiders you will be ok, and killing the Great Woowamp that drops the int items wont give you bad faction with Overthere, dont bother with the Great Woowamp yet wait till you are higher in lvl.<br>Get on the boat in TD to go to Overthere dont worry you are very safe there if you are a evil class which you are Necro.  Now get a map of the next 3zones : Overthere, Frontier Mountains, and one of the Lake of ill omen.  When you get to Overthere bind yourself wont really matter where just do it.  Then get your gather shadows out so you dont agro the big scary tigers and such.  Go to the Frontier mountains and try to get a sow.<br>Now run Left when you zone into Frontier mountains and keep running with you gathershadows (your invis) only thing is Giant tumps can see through it so becareful you might come across 2 of them but easy to avoid :) get to the lake with the map you have.  Once you are in the lake bind yourself again right by the zone.  Now if you are lvl 20-21 you dont need to go the Windmill its really a waste of time.  Just stay near the FM zone get into a group at either the Backdoor to the Sarnak fort or a group at the Front door.<br>You will get great exp at either one. Now dont forget you have your bind and gate spell, you will not make a great deal of pp in the Lake zone but in the FM zone you will.  When you bind in the Lake and you want to call it a day and bank well you cant go to the Iksar city or Fiornia Via, so start shouting for a Port nearest your city, Ports are about 10pp and you will make about 50-70pp in the lake on a good day so if you need to get something from the bank you dont have to risk going through FM and Overthere dont be cheap just pay the 10pp for a port.  When you get into FM you will be able to loot Legchoppers and other heavy items that sell for 30-60pp in your city or East Commons, Gating out of where ever you are back to the lake bind point will save time and the risk of dieing.  Try to get into a group with people either 2lvls above you and 2 below anything higher then you will take more of the exp that us necros deserve.  When you finally ding lvl 24 you will have a few new spells coming very nice and you will feel like a better necro because of the DD spell you get does a whole 160dd woot, now you can either stay in the Lake or go into FM and make a ton of plat and great loot while you get exp too.  Now the exp off the giants is not all that great you will see when you get in there.  But you will still lvl very fast.  Stay in there until you hit lvl 30 by then you will have so much Plat that you can either by another nice robe or your very expensive spells in the later lvls.  When you hit lvl 30 go to Overthere again and stay there until you hit lvl 39. Good luck :)<br><br>Yomega lvl 40 NEC<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
